[3] Germany ex Sierra Leone: 2nd evacuated case


Ebola Virus Disease, Germany, ex Sierra Leone, HCW
--------------------------------------------------
I would like to send you a reminder about the case of an international staff doctor working at Emergency ONG Ebola Treatment Centre in Sierra Leone who fell ill with ebolavirus and subsequently medevac'd to Germany. The Italian website of the ONG reporting as following:
http://www.emergency.it/comunicati-stampa/ebola-un-medico-di-emergency-in-sierra-leone-positivo-al-virus-2-ottobre-2014.html
BBC on Germany MEDEVAC: http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-29473623 [see below]

This also to highlight that despite the ebolavirus hit at the centre of USA's wealthiest region, other people and other countries are facing issues with infected [evacuated] patients.

